summary: Successfully resolved all merge conflicts by adopting the more complete, production-ready code from the main branch. The main branch had comprehensive configuration management, better database models, proper dependency injection, and enhanced alembic setup compared to the feature branch's simpler implementation.
strategyUsed: Analyzed each conflict and consistently chose the main branch version which contained more complete features including: comprehensive pydantic-based configuration with validation, advanced database connection pooling, proper async support, enhanced model definitions with better constraints and relationships, and production-ready alembic migrations. The main branch code was systematically more mature and feature-complete for F1 prediction analytics.
